def: The right description of things. [R.] Fotherby.
consisting of, containing, or characterized by, laterite; as,lateritic formations.
To make irreligious; to turn from religion. [R.]He would dereligionize men beyond all others. De Quincey.
The last reef in a fore-and-aft sail, taken to steady the ship.
The state or character of being crotchety, or whimsical.This belief in rightness is a kind of conscientiousness, and when itdegenerates it becomes crotchetiness. J. Grote.
A microscopic cell in the structure of an egg, animal, orplant.
Having the form of a beak.
Of or pertaining to forests; as, forestal rights.
